{{Subspeciesbox | name = Ornate spider monkey<ref name=msw3>{{MSW3 Groves|id=12100402}}</ref> | image = Panama spider monkey, Costa Rica.JPG | status = EN | status_system = IUCN3.1 | status_ref = <ref name=iucn>{{IUCN2011.2|assessor=Cuarón, A.D.|assessor2=Morales, A.|assessor3=Shedden, A.|assessor4=Rodriguez-Luna, E.|assessor5=de Grammont, P.C.|last-assessor-amp=yes|year=2008|id=2289|title=Ateles geoffroyi ssp. ornatus|version=2011.2|downloaded=19 January 2012}}</ref> | genus = Ateles | species = geoffroyi | species_link = Geoffroy's spider monkey | subspecies = ornatus | authority = ([[John Edward Gray|Gray]], 1870) | synonyms = *''azuerensis'' Bole, 1937 *''panamensis'' Kellogg and Golman, 1944 }}
The '''ornate spider monkey''' (''Ateles geoffroyi ornatus''), is a subspecies of [[Geoffroy's spider monkey]], a type of [[New World monkey]],<ref name=msw3/> from [[Central America]], native to [[Costa Rica]] and [[Panama]].<ref name=iucn/><ref name=iucn-panamensis>{{IUCN2007|assessor=Rylands, A.|assessor2=Members of the Primate Specialist Group|last-assessor-amp=yes|year=2003|id=2281|title=Ateles geoffroyi ''ssp.'' panamensis|downloaded=2008-07-26}}</ref><ref name=iucn-azuerensis>{{IUCN2007|assessor=Rylands, A.|assessor2=Members of the Primate Specialist Group|last-assessor-amp=yes|year=2003|id=2286|title=Ateles geoffroyi ''ssp.'' azuerensis|downloaded=2008-07-26}}</ref> Other common names for this subspecies include the '''brilliant spider monkey''', the '''common spider monkey''', the '''red spider monkey''', the '''Panama spider ape''', and the '''[[Azuero Spider Monkey|Azuero spider monkey]]''', the latter two of which were previously thought to be distinct subspecies ''panamensis'' and ''azuerensis'', respectively.<ref name=msw3/>
[[Image:Juvenile spider monkey, Costa Rica.JPG|thumb|left|Female 22-month-old juvenile ''A. g. ornatus'' in a southern [[Costa Rica]] [[wildlife rehabilitation]] center. As a juvenile, her face is light colored, but it will darken upon sexual maturity.]]
